comments.body: Yes, maddening indeed. There seems to be quite a bit of overlap in the western states, so I'm basing my ID on the DFW, where that large black area pushes down into the yellow spot.  My understanding is that on the Eastern this black would be minimal. There are differences to the underwing, but I'm not confident with that ID.
I find this split maddening. Not sure where Easterns begin. But, if all of Mexico is Western, I could have swore so went Texas. I think this is a Western. Let’s wait for others to ring in.
